value.name: 17 (number) - Wikipedia
value.snippet: 17 is the seventh prime number, which makes seventeen the fourth super-prime, as seven is itself prime. The next prime is 19, with which it forms a twin prime. [1] It is a cousin prime with 13 and a sexy prime with 11 and 23. [2] [3] It is an emirp, and more specifically a permutable prime with 71, both of which are also supersingular primes.

value.snippet: Der er to størrelser, og de mindste passer til biler som f.eks. VW Polo, mens de lidt større matcher nogle udgaver af Opel Astra, Peugeot 3008 og Mercedes-Benz A-klasse.
